Please note that under our agreement, applicable laws and regulations, we are unable to proceed with the deletion of your personal data and at the same time provide you with our services. If you wish to continue having an account and trade with us and generally make use of our services, please note that at the same time we will continue to collect and process your personal data.

IMPORTANT NOTE: Prior to submitting a Deletion of Account and Personal Data request, you will need to (i) close any remaining open positions and (ii) withdraw any balance credited to your account. Otherwise we will be unable to proceed with your request.

If you choose to DELETE your account and ALL your personal data:\10(i) You will not be able to access your account nor restore your account;\10(ii) You will not be able to execute any transactions or trade or make any use of the IQ Option services; and\10(iii) Upon completion of our review, our contractual relationship shall be terminated.\10If you wish to inquire on any other matter relating to personal data, please contact us as prescribed in the Privacy Policy.

The \"Traders\' Sentiment\" widget displays the current Call/Put ratio. For example, if the widget is 70% red, it means that at this point 70% of traders went \"Put\" and only 30% went \"Call\".

ADX is used to quantify trend strength. The calculations are based on a moving average of price range expansion over a given period of time. The default setting is 14 bars, although other time periods can be used. When the +Di is above the –Di, prices are moving up, and ADX measures the strength of the uptrend. When the –Di is above the +Di, prices are moving down, and ADX measures the strength of the downtrend.

Provides a useful visual tool for trend recognition and trade entry timing. The three lines stretched apart and moving higher or lower denote trending periods in which long or short positions should be maintained and managed.
ATR is a chart analysis tool for keeping an eye on volatility caused by price gaps or limit moves. It is an indicator which is best used as a compliment to more price direction driven indicators.

Awesome Oscillator is an indicator used to measure market momentum. AO calculates the difference of a 34 Period and 5 Period Simple Moving Averages. It is generally used to affirm trends or to anticipate possible reversals.

Bollinger Bands belong to the category of trend indicators. They reflect the dynamic range of the price movement. With their help, many traders determine the relative position of the price within the selected time interval, as well as identify possible market entry points and the level of correctional waves when the price rebounds from the indicator lines.

CCI is a momentum oscillator used in technical analysis primarily to identify overbought and oversold levels by measuring an instrument\'s variations away from its statistical mean. Moreover, CCI is often used to find reversals as well as divergences. Originally, the indicator was designed to be used for identifying trends in commodities, however it is now used in a wide range of financial instruments.

Fractal is an indicator used to indicate market reversal points. Fractal comprises of five consecutive bar, where a middle bar always has a higher high or lower low than the two preceding bars and the two following bars. The main purpose of Fractal indicator is to indicate market reversal points.

Can be used to identify trend momentum, direction, and duration. MACD employs two Moving Averages of varying lengths (which are lagging indicators) to identify trend direction and duration. Then, MACD takes the difference in values between those two Moving Averages (MACD line) and an exponential moving averages of those Moving Averages (Signal Line) and plots that difference between the two lines as a histogram which oscillates above and below a center Base Line. The histogram is used as a good indication of a security\'s momentum.

Moving Averages is a group of technical indicators that are commonly used to determine the current trend. The most popular averages are the Simple Moving Average (SMA), the Weighted (WMA), the Exponential (EMA), and the Smoothed Simple Moving Average (SSMA). Moving Averages are used in other technical analysis indicators such as Bollinger Bands, Alligator, MACD, and Awesome Oscillator.

Parabolic SAR is a time and price technical analysis tool primarily used to identify points of potential stops and reversals. In fact, the SAR in Parabolic SAR stands for \"Stop and Reverse\". The indicator\'s calculations create a parabola which is located below price during a Bullish Trend and above Price during a Bearish Trend. Acceleration Factor alters the sensitivity of the SAR.

A well versed momentum based oscillator, which is used to measure the velocity as well as the magnitude of directional price movements. It provides a visual mean to monitor both the current, as well as historical, strength and weakness of a particular market. The strength or weakness is based on closing prices over the duration of a specified trading period, creating a reliable metric of price and momentum changes.

Stochastic is a momentum indicator comparing the closing price of a security to the range of its prices over a certain period of time. The sensitivity of the oscillator to market movements is reducible by adjusting that time period or by taking a moving average of the result.
